## After

<img width="683" height="189" alt="Screenshot 2026-01-24 at 10 56 52 AM" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8ff9c1e1-a0d6-4c19-b9c8-f5fbf54c8d18" />

Should this be added to this PR? or would it be better to separate it?

Thanks for the updates. I think I would find this more clear if you localized the updates to `create_decimal`, e.g.:

```py
@staticmethod
def _create_decimal(value):
    if isinstance(value, int):
        return decimal.Decimal(value)
    return decimal.Context(prec=15).create_decimal_from_float(value)
```

@VIZZARD-X 

This is a great start, but I think it could be refined a bit before it's ready. 

Please do remember my comments are just one man's opinion. I hope they provide food for thought though, and are helpful.

commits.message:
Refs #36770 -- Guarded against an endless wait in LiveServerThread.terminate().

terminate() shouldn't assume the main server was started. (A deadlock
from mishandling of in-memory SQLite databases may have occurred.)
